Package: lazychromosomes
Type: Package
Title: Quantitative Evaluation Of Chromosome Laziness From Kinetochore Tracks
Version: 0.1.0
Author: c(person("Jonathan", "Harrison", email = "jonathan.u.harrison@warwick.ac.uk", role = c("cre","aut"))
Description: Assess errors in chromosome segregation quantitatively by computing laziness of segregating chromosomes. The laziness is a statistic that considers the distance of a segregating chromosome from its corresponding daughter cell, scaled by the spread of the cluster.
License: GLP-3
Depends:
    R (>= 3.5.0)
Imports:
    dplyr (>= 1.0.0), zoo (>= 1.8.0)
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true    
